request.description:
Get a list of all available MCP servers on the platform.

Returns an array of server objects with id, status, and metadata.

Example response:
{
  "servers": [ {"id": "math-server", ...}, {"id": "matallo-server", ...}, ... ]
}

Get a list of all available tools for the specified MCP server.

Path Variable:
- server-id (string, required): The ID of the MCP server (e.g., math-server, matallo-server, idosalomon-server).

Returns an array of tool objects with name, description, and inputSchema.

Example response:
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "name": "multiply",
      "description": "Multiply two numbers",
      "inputSchema": { ... }
    },
    ...
  ]
}
